<HEADLINE>
FORMER ACTING MAYOR LANDS PRESIDENTIAL OFFICE POST
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Feb. 9 (CNA) 02/09/07  19:31:30 (By Lilian Wu)
</P>
<P>
President Chen Shui-bian announced several major appointments
Friday, including that of Chen Chi-mai, a former legislator and
former Kaohsiung acting mayor, who will serve as deputy
secretary-general of the Presidential Office.
</P>
<P>
Chen Chi-mai will fill the vacancy left by Liu Shih-feng, who
will take the new post of deputy secretary-general of the
National Security Council.
</P>
<P>
In addition, National Security Council Deputy Secretary-general
Wang Hsi-tien will serve as deputy director of the National
Security Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Chen Chi-mai served as acting Kaohsiung mayor in 2005 before
resigning to take responsibility for a riot in late August that
year by Thai laborers working for Kaohsiung's mass rapid transit
system to protest against poor treatment and inhumane management.
</P>
<P>
The appointments will take effect Feb. 12.
</P>
